      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "BLESSED RAIN (8) could not have been more impressive last start in her a flying 22.59 win at this track over 400m. Has the ability and looks hard to top. CHAVERO (1) was fresh up last time at Bendigo where he finished fifth (24.26) in a Grade 5 H. Has a strong winning record here at this journey. Comes out of a solid form race last start. A big run wouldn't surprise. LIGHTNING JEWEL (6) goes very well this course and distance starting 21 times for 12 wins and four minors. In the money last time at Geelong (22.58) in a Grade 5, finishing a 1.3 lengths second. With even luck and a clean start can sneak into the finish. ASTON GOZO (7) should be thereabouts after filling a top-three spot most recently.",
